a. Despite their specificities, these contexts present us with an opportunity to analyze similar mnemonic dynamics and to recognize the political impact of dissenting artistic production. Crossing disciplinary boundaries, the book intervenes in debates over collective responsibility, historical injustice, and the aesthetics of violence within political theory, memory studies, social epistemology, and transitional justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAccomplices. 0aCollective memoryxPolitical aspects. 0aCollective memory. 0aMemoryxPolitical aspects. 0aResponsibility. 0aRestorative justice. 0aSocial justice. 0aViolencexPolitical aspectsxPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Social.2bisacsh  aApartheid South Africa.  aCommunist Romania.  aVichy France.  acomplicity.  amnemonic care.  amnemonic erasures.  apolitical memory.  aprosthetic world-traveling.  aresistance.  aseductive sabotage.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363013040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503630130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503630130/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  